metadata.name: Encapsulated #297
metadata.description:
Have you ever felt fear? Have you ever felt tired? Have you ever felt trapped and watched? The bars of the big cities are supposed to bring us protection, but in the end, we are encapsulated in this big prison.

This project was made thinking about that feeling of prison ourselves and will participate in the #fxhashturnsone event. 

Fully made with p5.js and p5.grain

metadata.name: The Spectrum Of Nature #161
metadata.description:
*\_../*`¬-’\/*`¬’’¬`*\/’-¬`*\.._/*

Nature, nature, evolving might… Silent inventor, always right.
Where is the edge of nature and where do we begin?  
What is of nature and what is of man? 
Isn't everything made by nature's hands?

To know more about the concept and technicalities of this piece, see the fxtext article “The spectrum of nature - a short making of”. Link at the bottom. If you’d rather just ignore my personal meaning, feel free to skip the article. 

\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\

Basic info:
The piece comes in possible portrait or landscape versions. Both have a relative size of 1 by 1.5. So the initial render will be 1000px wide and 1500px high for portrait. And 1500x1000 for landscape. With the ability to scale this up (see below).

The piece uses WebGL, so will perform much better with a graphics card. A faster computer will obviously be better, though I've done my very best to make it fast and efficient for any old laptop. My hope is that you will find the render process quick and enjoyable for the amount of detail that’s present. 

../’`*’`\../’`*’`\../’`*’`\../’`*’`\../’`*’`\..

Controls:
Press the [s] key to save the initial render. You will need to wait a few seconds after all the elements have stopped loading. A box will pop up in the top left saying “done” for 4 seconds when it’s ready. For the [s] key to work you may need to open in a new tab. But can right click save otherwise.

Larger sizes:
Press the [2-9] keys to save a resolution of that key size. So [2] saves a 2000x3000 size image, [9] saves a 9000x13500 size image etc. Unless you are making some very large prints you probably won’t need more than 4k (even 2-3k is big). Though the option is there. 

There may be slight variations in the textures for the larger renders, this is because the shader code has to redraw the textures at the higher pixel resolution, and getting the textures where they sit is more of an art than a science. All the elements remain exact however. 

/*/*/*/*/*/*/*/*/*/*/*/*/*/*/*/*/*/*

Made with javascript and some small extra code:
A palette creator by @nathansonic
Noisejs - github.com/josephg/noisejs - Perlin noise generator
Twgl - github.com/greggman/twgl.js - A small webGL helper.

metadata.name: Play with lines #2 #51
metadata.description:
Play with lines
This collection is the result of my play with the lines I drew with the tablet in an unbalanced state of mind.
And combining these lines with digital paintings in the background


This set has 7 layers
The first and last layer of the background and frame
The third layer of digital painting
The second layer of valve patterns
And three layers of lines that I have designed each one alone

metadata.name: GEOMETRIC #61
metadata.description:
Following the search for formal simplification, where everything is built using simple geometric figures, aggregations to planes and colors, lights and shadows.

Features:
PALLETS
In total, the work has 31 different color palettes, with probability percentages ranging from 2% to 7%.

FORMS
The images are structured using just four simple shapes (square, rectangle, circle and triangle) proportional to each other.

The use of each of the forms follows six different combination patterns.

VECTOR
Rectangular elements can have two orientations (horizontal or vertical).

SATURATION
In total, four levels of color saturation are applied, ranging from 25% to 100%.

CANVAS
Altogether there are four different canvas formats, in the following proportions: 1x2, 2x3, 3x4 and 1x1.

FRAGMENTATION AND DENSITY
Finally, the elements are combined from four stages of fragmentation and five levels of density.

November 14, 2022.

Paivei's generative token made with p5js, in celebration of the first anniversary of FxHash.

 #fxhashturnsone

"You know what I want to say."

敬自由

metadata.name: 7VV1N5 #387
metadata.description:
GO BIG OR GO HOME.

After a week of minimalism code, our hero, the handsome artist Daniel, decided he needed something involving maximalism to reset the balance. Finding pairs to put together is satisfying.

Images will take 6-9 seconds to display and refresh between window resizing.

Use the z key or single click/tap to switch to "zoom" mode, which zooms in and fills the viewport; use z & tap/click to cycle through views. Use x and double-click/tap to go back to square mode.

Note: It doesn't work on Internet Explorer, because Microsoft. iOS is faster than Android.

-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

z, click, tap - Switch to & cycle "zoom" mode
x, double-click, double-tap - Switch back out of "zoom" mode.
h - Toggle high-res (slow)
s - Download and save image (takes a few seconds, longer for high-res)

"You know what I want to say."

metadata.name: Bento Boxes #246
metadata.description:
Everybody needs a bento box in the cryptowinter.
The project calls for an adopted nostalgia of little kids that has been handed bento box by their parents before school— a little moment of protected comfort before heading out for an adventure.

• • •

The first collaboration project of MEK.txt and IceRain in FXHash. A work based on MEK.txt’s “The Bento Boxes” and IceRain’s excellent codes, Bento Boxes aims to be a fun visual and code exploration project on the generative art corridor. Pure code, no libraries.

Bento Boxes deconstructed the visual system on MEK.txt's artwork, titled almost similarly, “The Bento Boxes”. Rebuilt it from scratch with codes, adding variants of colours and shapes— without losing the strong characteristics of the base artwork.

metadata.name: Impressions of Order #119
metadata.description:
‘Impressions of Order’ is a collection of 300 generative compositions. 

Inspired by 90s ROM cartridges, server farms and future cityscapes this project explores perception and documentation of ‘order’ within complex systems. 

--------------------------------------------------------

This artwork is best enjoyed in high-resolution so that the subtle layering, colour shifts, variation in hard and soft edges, faint impressions of construction, and the various low-probability glitchy events can be fully appreciated. 

By default, the artwork will load in 2K resolution (1400 x 2000 px). It is recommended that you view the work in 4K or 6K to appreciate the finer details. 

The keyboard buttons: “2”, “4”, and “6” can be pressed to change the resolution to 2K, 4K and 6K resolution accordingly. 

To download an image at its current resolution, press the keyboard button “S”.

--------------------------------------------------------

Artwork created with p5.js

@nbswwit
Sept 2022

metadata.name: Knockout #173
metadata.description:
An exploration of screen printing techniques and how these effects can be achieved in generative work. The halftone effect works by placing very small dots next to each other to give the illusion of new shades and hues. Each Knockout samples three colors for the main composition and runs small sections of the canvas back through the machine after shuffling the base palette. The secondary passes vary in size, creating interesting emergent patterns on the overlap.

Press 's' in live view to save a .png

Built and tested with Chrome on Apple silicon. Some outputs may take up to 20s on slower machines.

Created with p5.js and chroma.js

metadata.name: In Due Time #164
metadata.description:
“In Due Time” is a collaborative generative collection between artists Melissa Wiederrecht and Amber Vittoria. Inspired by Wiederrecht’s mastery of line and Vittoria’s notable palette, this 1/1/250 series captures the present moment. It serves as a reminder that we are more similar than we are different, leveraging homogeneous shapes to create distinctive compositions.

Vittoria’s poem for the collection:

“In Due Time”
We will all become
Particles dancing
Across the skyline.

The artwork listed is indeed authentic, created by, and copyright to artists Melissa Wiederrecht and Amber Vittoria; the purchase of this NFT is a purchase of the asset, not of the copyright.

-------------------------------------------

To save a high-resolution image for printing, click “open” under the image on the page for your token, and then hit:

Digits “1” through “9” to get an image that is 1000 through 9000px tall.  This may take a while, depending on the size and your computer, so please be patient.
